Five students from Oriwo Secondary School, Rachuonyo North subcounty, have been arrested. They have been linked to a school fire that razed a dormitory on Monday. The suspects will appear at the Oyugis law courts today to answer to arson charges. Police chief Philip Chirchir said the students were arrested after thorough investigations. He said they are also investigating the fire at Gendia High School in the same subcounty. One dormitory was destroyed. The 100-bed capacity dormitory caught fire at 5.30am, when students were in class for morning studies. Chirchir said he will meet all scool heads to discuss the fires.